The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Chennai, June 23 (PTI): One person was killed and another grievously injured when a crane crashed on them during airport expansion work near the domestic terminal.          
	Selvamani, 45, of north Chennai, died on the way to the hospital. Airport officials said they were probing the cause of the accident.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Central Vigilance Commission has sought amendment of a law that bars registration of cases against judges, members of the armed forces and senior public servants without the Centres permission. The anti-corruption watchdog has also asked the government to increase the number of special courts for faster disposal of corruption cases.                  
	 Raipur: One of the tyres of a Kingfisher flight carrying 75 people burst during touchdown at Mana airport in Raipur but the pilots pulled the brakes and averted an accident. Most of the passengers on the Aizawl-Hyderabad flight that stops at Calcutta and Raipur were from Calcutta. The onward flight to Hyderabad was cancelled.                  
	 Bareilly (PTI): Five people suffocated to death in an open biogas plant in Uttar Pradesh on Wednesday. When Pooja, 20, accidentally fell into an abandoned biogas plant, four others jumped in one after the other to try to save her                  
	 Vadodara (PTI): Chief minister Narendra Modi has asked Pakistan-bound home minister P. Chidambaram and foreign secretary Nirupama Rao to press for the release of more than 550 Gujarati fishermen in Pakistani jails.                  
	 Melbourne (PTI): The jury hearing the trial of Indian-origin surgeon Jayant Patel for manslaughter is expected to state its verdict soon. After hearing the case for 14 weeks and examining evidence from more than 75 witnesses in the trial of 60-year-old Patel, the jury of six men and six women has retired to consider its verdict.
                                                                                                                                              
